<!-- ================= BODY ================= -->
<section class="bg-[var(--white)]">
  <div class="max-w-[1180px] mx-auto px-6 pb-24">
    <div class="tm-wrap tm-prose">

      <div class="tm-callout">
        <p>This Privacy Policy explains how <strong>OTP, LLC</strong> ("OTP," "we," "us," or "our"), a New Jersey limited liability company, collects, uses, shares, and protects information in connection with the website at <strong>orgtp.com</strong> and the OTP platform, applications, APIs, and related services (the "Service"). It works alongside our <a href="/terms">Terms of Service</a>. By using the Service, you agree to this Policy.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 id="info-we-collect">1. Information We Collect</h2>
      <h3>Information you provide</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Account &amp; profile:</strong> name, email address, organization name, role, and credentials, handled through our authentication provider.</li>
        <li><strong>Customer Content:</strong> the data you submit to the Service, including org charts, seats, KPIs, scorecards, meetings, Rocks, issues, to-dos, Organizational Operating System ("OOS") files, and other content.</li>
        <li><strong>Communications:</strong> messages you send us, support requests, and survey responses.</li>
        <li><strong>Payment information:</strong> billing details, processed by our third-party payment provider; we do not store full card numbers.</li>
      </ul>
      <h3>Information collected automatically</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Usage data:</strong> pages viewed, features used, actions taken, and timestamps.</li>
        <li><strong>Device &amp; log data:</strong> IP address, browser type, device identifiers, and similar technical information.</li>
        <li><strong>Cookies &amp; similar technologies:</strong> used to keep you signed in, remember preferences, and understand usage. You can control cookies through your browser settings.</li>
      </ul>
      <h3>Information from third parties</h3>
      <p>If you connect a third-party integration (for example, email, calendar, or messaging tools), we receive information from those services as authorized by you.</p>

      <h2 id="how-we-use">2. How We Use Information</h2>
      <p>We use information to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>provide, operate, maintain, and secure the Service;</li>
        <li>create accounts and authenticate users;</li>
        <li>generate AI-assisted summaries, suggestions, learnings, and other output;</li>
        <li>send service, transactional, and (where consented) marketing communications;</li>
        <li>process payments and manage subscriptions;</li>
        <li>analyze usage to improve and develop the Service;</li>
        <li>detect, prevent, and respond to fraud, abuse, and security issues; and</li>
        <li>comply with legal obligations and enforce our Terms.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="communications">3. Communications &amp; Consent</h2>
      <p>By creating an account, you opt in to receive communications from OTP, including service and transactional messages and, where applicable, product updates and marketing messages, as described in our <a href="/terms">Terms of Service</a>. Service-related messages are necessary to operate your account. You may opt out of <strong>marketing</strong> messages at any time using the unsubscribe link in those messages or by contacting <a href="mailto:support@orgtp.com">support@orgtp.com</a>; we will still send you service-related messages.</p>

      <h2 id="ai">4. AI Features</h2>
      <p>The Service uses artificial intelligence to process Customer Content and generate output. Content may be processed by trusted third-party AI providers acting on our behalf under contractual confidentiality and security obligations. We do not sell your Customer Content. AI output may be inaccurate and should be reviewed before you rely on it.</p>

      <h2 id="cross-org">5. Cross-Organization Intelligence</h2>
      <p>A core purpose of OTP is to share what works across organizations. When you publish an OOS file or coordination learning, or otherwise make content public within the Service, that content may be visible to and used by other users as described in the Service. We may also surface generalized, de-identified learnings derived from use of the Service across organizations. If your organization is on a <strong>Private</strong> plan or marks content as private, that content is excluded from cross-organization surfaces in accordance with our privacy controls.</p>

      <h2 id="sharing">6. How We Share Information</h2>
      <p>We do not sell your personal information. We share information only:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>With service providers</strong> (such as hosting, authentication, payment processing, analytics, email delivery, and AI providers) who process data on our behalf under appropriate safeguards;</li>
        <li><strong>Within your organization</strong> — other members of your organization may see Customer Content according to their roles and permissions;</li>
        <li><strong>For published or public content</strong> as described in Section 5;</li>
        <li><strong>For legal reasons</strong> — to comply with law, respond to lawful requests, or protect the rights, safety, and property of OTP, our users, or others; and</li>
        <li><strong>In a business transfer</strong> — in connection with a merger, acquisition, financing, or sale of assets, subject to this Policy.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="retention">7. Data Retention</h2>
      <p>We retain information for as long as your account is active and as needed to provide the Service, comply with legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce our agreements. When information is no longer needed, we delete or de-identify it. You may request deletion of your account and associated personal information as described below.</p>

      <h2 id="security">8. Security</h2>
      <p>We use administrative, technical, and physical safeguards designed to protect information, including encryption in transit and access controls. No method of transmission or storage is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>

      <h2 id="your-rights">9. Your Rights &amp; Choices</h2>
      <p>Depending on where you live, you may have rights to access, correct, delete, or port your personal information, to opt out of certain processing, and to withdraw consent. To exercise these rights, contact us at <a href="mailto:support@orgtp.com">support@orgtp.com</a>. We will respond as required by applicable law and will not discriminate against you for exercising your rights.</p>
      <h3>U.S. state privacy rights</h3>
      <p>Residents of certain U.S. states may have additional rights regarding their personal information. We do not sell personal information or share it for cross-context behavioral advertising as those terms are defined under applicable state law.</p>
      <h3>EU/UK users</h3>
      <p>Where the GDPR or UK GDPR applies, we process personal data on the legal bases of consent, performance of a contract, our legitimate interests, and compliance with legal obligations. You may have the right to lodge a complaint with your local supervisory authority.</p>

      <h2 id="children">10. Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>The Service is not directed to children under 18, and we do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe a child has provided us information, contact us and we will delete it.</p>

      <h2 id="international">11. International Data Transfers</h2>
      <p>OTP is based in the United States, and information may be processed and stored in the United States and other countries. Where required, we use appropriate safeguards for international transfers.</p>

      <h2 id="changes">12. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>We may update this Policy from time to time. If we make material changes, we will provide notice through the Service or by email. Your continued use of the Service after changes take effect constitutes acceptance of the revised Policy.</p>

      <h2 id="contact">13. Contact Us</h2>
      <p>Questions about this Policy or your information? Contact <strong>OTP, LLC</strong> at <a href="mailto:support@orgtp.com">support@orgtp.com</a>.</p>

      <p class="text-[12px] mt-12" style="color:var(--ink-faint, #98a2b3);">OTP, LLC · New Jersey, USA · orgtp.com</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
